    "body": "Minimal reproduction:\r\n\r\n```js\r\n  // push0 push0 mstore push0\r\n  const bytecode = \"0x5F5F525F\"\r\n\r\n  const [account] = await network.provider.send(\"eth_accounts\", [])\r\n\r\n  const address = \"0x1234567890123456789012345678901234567890\"\r\n\r\n  await network.provider.send(\"hardhat_setCode\", [address, bytecode])\r\n\r\n  const tx = await network.provider.send(\"eth_sendTransaction\", [{\r\n    from: account,\r\n    to: address\r\n  }])\r\n\r\n  const trace = await network.provider.send(\"debug_traceTransaction\", [tx])\r\n\r\n  console.log(JSON.stringify(trace, null, 2))\r\n```\r\n\r\nThat bytecode pushes two 0s to the stack and executes a `MSTORE`, and the resulting memory entry, instead of having a length of 1, has a length of 256. That's a big clue of what can be going on here.",
